Talking with @berniceradle about her two cheap old house renovations. One a 10k house she bought and a 20k dollar house.

And finance tips like creative ways to afford your cheap old house go with the local bank, renovation loans, first time buyer programs, and renting out Airbnb rooms to afford projects on your house.

Ethan and I are beyond excited to welcome Ryan Gustafson of @thedeadtongues to our #CelebrationofHome concert series. We’ve been long-time fans of his music, and were honored and humbled when he offered to perform his brand new song, “Peaceful Ambassador” in this very special set just for all of you. It’s from from his new album, “Transmigration Blues,” which is coming out ‪6/26‬ and explores, in his own words, “the moments weaving between uncertainty and discovery.” (well, is that ever timely!)
.
We started our Celebration of Home series back when the world first shut down, and we realized that so many of our favorite musicians would likely be deeply affected by the shutdown. Concerts and other very large social gatherings will likely be the last things to come back to normal. And yet ironically, Ethan and I have found our salvation during this time in music. These musicians have voluntarily given their time to perform for us, and we’re so grateful to be able to share their music with all of you! The best gift you can give back to @thedeadtongues would be a follow or an album purchase from thedeadtongues.com‬
.
In the years since we’ve been running this account, we’ve noticed that musicians and other professional creatives make up a large percentage of our audience. This has not come as a surprise - it takes a creative mind to see the beauty in many of the homes we share. We’re certain you’ll see as much beauty as we do in @thedeadtongues and hope you enjoy it! Thank you Ryan!

node.text:
It would be hard to convey in writing just how special this one is for me and Ethan. We started listening to @bowerbirdsmusic when we were first dating, and besides knowing every single lyric to every single album by heart (Phil is a pretty powerful lyricist), two of his songs quite literally helped inspire this feed. One, “In the Yard,” perfectly encapsulates the feeling of loving a place despite its quirks. “It may not be a grand parade of snow capped peaks...” but it’s ours.
.
The other, “House of Diamonds” (the 3rd song Phil plays in the concert) is one of my favorite songs all of time. Actually, it’s my anthem. If there’s anything I’ve preached on this feed, it’s that the American dream doesn’t have to look any one particular way.
.
“Your sister marries a nice young man; And they build a house of diamonds. But the sun is snuffed by the curtains; Can someone come untie you? But there is too much work to do. Yes, they all admire you.

You are free; You are already free.

You are free from the greed of your culture; You are free from the lust for the luster; Of the diamond houses in the city's cluster; From your own ego, from your own blunder.

Yes, you own the stars, you own the thunder
But you have to share it all;
Yes, you own the stars, you own the thunder
But you have to share.
You are free;
You are already free.”
.
Old houses in need, the ones with soul — the ones others have forgotten — are my stars and my thunder.

Phil has just released two new singles — "Endless Chase" and "Hazel Eyes" — and they have been totally worth the wait.

Anyway, I could go on and on, but at the risk of getting too sentimental about all of this, I’ll just leave it at this: Enjoy @bowerbirdsmusic - we’re honored to have him!

When Ethan and I first heard @bedouinemusic sing her song "Bird", we were stunned. Mesmerized. And she's been on steady rotation in our house ever since, filling our home with a hauntingly beautiful vintage sound (It is bossa nova? Folk? We can't tell. But it's SO good.) There's something in her voice that reminds us of the soul of old homes - which wasn't as surprising once we found out she lives in one. We hope you fall in love with her voice tonight as our #celebrationofhome concert series continues. Please enjoy, and give her a follow as thanks for being such a light in our lives (and now yours, too!)

If you love her, go give her a follow! All of the musicians performing in our series are currently unable to perform live or rely on any of their usual means of income during quarantine. And yet, their voices are helping so many of us in this critical moment. Thank you @swordsdaughter for being YOU!

218 E Main St, Wabash, IN — I have yet to meet an Italianate I didn’t fall deeply in love with 😍Listed by Robert Lundquist of Lundquist Appraisals & Real Estate Services, Inc via @indianalandmarks “Diamond in the rough!! Check out this imposing 19 room Victorian home with lots of bedrooms, 4 full baths, 3 fireplaces located on a spacious double lot in the East Wabash Historic District.  Built for local banker Frank Morse in 1885, this house has all the hallmarks of the grand Italianate style. The  interior of the home offers loads of old house charm including a winding walnut staircase, 3 fireplaces, ornate trim and more.  The exterior retains its original bracketed cornice, open front porch and sturdy brick construction. The house needs major restoration to bring back its luster but the result will be a one-of-a-kind property.  This home is offered by Indiana Landmarks who requires the house be used as a single family home and has a protective covenant on the exterior.  Utilities are all on and functional. Hot water heat was winterized this spring after occupants moved out. Sellers Indiana Landmarks will consider any reasonable offers however do require buyers to agree to be an owner occupant have a reasonable renovation plan to restore this beauty back to life and agree to Exterior Historical Covenants. Also has a 20' x 28' addition on the rear of the home.” — link at cheapoldhouses.com #cheapoldhousesin

You instantly will see into the spacious living room with hardwood floors and crown molding. The dining has hardwood floors and an ornamental fireplace. The kitchen is a nice size and is ready for you to make it your dream kitchen. Also included on the first level is a convenient half bath. The second level features a spacious hallway with built-in cabinets. There are three bedrooms and a full bath on this level. The bathroom has all new tile - the floor is a honeycomb pattern. The main bedroom is very spacious and use to be two bedrooms. The third floor has a full bath, bedroom and a walk-in closet. It would make a great master. There is an unfinished part on the third floor that would make a great home office once completed. The exterior of the home features a two car detached garage and a brick patio.” — link at cheapoldhouses.com #cheapoldhousesny

node.text:
ALL ABOARD the Jeannie + Bill train! (I’m doing my best to drum up some good train puns, but I’m willing to face that Jeannie + Bill will always win in that department. If you don’t believe me, go follow @taylor.train.depot and thank me later.)
.
Ethan and I had been following these two for years before we were greenlit for the show, and getting to visit them in Edenton felt a bit like meeting up again with old friends after far too long.

JOIN US TONIGHT! Our Episode 8 recap with Jeannie + Bill will take place at 9pm EST on Instagram live. We’re going to talk all things train depot, including the layout and architectural details, both a direct result of the depot having been segregated when it was built in 1902. We’ll also discuss the challenges of turning a non-conventional building into a home (What do you keep? What do you change?), and the restoration of their exterior wood siding (which happened after the filming and can hopefully inspire others to toss out the aluminum and vinyl!)
.
See you there!

4906 W Washington Blvd, Milwaukee, WI — A fun history with this one! Listed for $399k by Michael Argeropoulos of Riverwest Realty Milwaukee. Located in the Washington/Hi Mount Boulevards Historical District, this spacious six bedroom home has a sun room, grand foyer, formal dining room, fireplace and indoor fountain. Hardwood floors, french doors, lead glass windows, arched doors and windows abound. Opulent vintage tiled bathrooms, butler's pantry, attached garage. Don't forget the pergola, slate roof and copper gutters and .28 acre lot! Great parks, restaurants, breweries, schools within walking distance. This fabulous home will thrive with your maintenance, attention and loving care. Sold in 'as-is' condition.” — link at cheapoldhouses.com #cheapoldhouseswi

Santo Adriano, Spain — Take me there!!! Listed at €42,000 (approx $49,551). “This unique building is based on an old mill from the 6th century located next to the tourist trail Senda del Oso, specifically as it passes through Sabadía, in Santo Adriano. Access is via a stone bridge over the Reguero de Sabadía, which makes it even more special. Several modifications have been carried out at different times, such as the porch that reproduces a cloister with several capitals or the addition of one more floor.
It has a constructed area of 72 m2 distributed over two floors, with a living room-kitchen with fireplace, a bedroom and a bathroom. On the 300 m2 plot with stone closure, it has a garden area and a well.”
